BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7PK2EBlCiRdresYVbIlBr
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260323T153920Z
DTSTART:20260323T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-23T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-23T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sTPkedPNTZoda9HjxDu5N
SUMMARY:Endless Opportunities: Volunteer Birthday Dreams
DTSTAMP:20260323T153920Z
DTSTART:20260323T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us in bringing joy\, dignity\, and celebration to children
	 experiencing homelessness through this Birthday Dreams service project. B
	irthday Dreams is a nonprofit organization dedicated to bringing hope\, jo
	y\, and a sense of self-worth to homeless children with the gift of a birt
	hday party\, partnering with more than 80 shelters across the Puget Sound 
	region to ensure every child feels loved and remembered on their special d
	ay. We’ll come together to assemble goody bags and curate other birthday i
	tems that are delivered to local shelters and families. These items help c
	reate a complete birthday experience—from party favors and treats to thoug
	htful supplies that make each child’s celebration feel magical and meaning
	ful.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/endless-opportunitie
	s-volunteer-birthday-dreams/18305982/2026-03-23T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Comm
	unity & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/endless-opportunities-vol
	unteer-birthday-dreams/18305982/2026-03-23T00
LOCATION:Stroum Jewish Community Center\, 3801 East Mercer Way\, Mercer Isl
	and\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
